This paper discusses the incorporation of human guidance into Reinforcement Learning, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper focuses on improving the learning process of agents through human guidance. The second likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper discusses the use of expert advice to improve the performance of agents. The third likely category is cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), as the paper explores the interaction between humans and agents in the learning process. The fourth likely category is cs.RO (Robotics), as the paper discusses the use of Reinforcement Learning in complex environments. The fifth likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), as the paper discusses the use of human guidance to improve the control of agents.
